thread.title: Prep Softball: Blair Oaks lands 7 on all-district team
thread.title_full: Prep Softball: Blair Oaks lands 7 on all-district team

author: News Tribune
title: Prep Softball: Blair Oaks lands 7 on all-district team
text:
Share 
WARDSVILLE — The Blair Oaks Lady Falcons landed seven players on the Class 2 District 9 team. 
The district champions had three more players named to the team than Eugene. Three Russellville players made the tournament team. Warsaw had two, while Versailles had one. 
Infield: Blair Oaks’ Carli Buschjost, Macyn Wilbers, Natalie Mudd and Sydney Wilde, Eugene’s Nola Polly, Warsaw’s Kylie McRoberts, Russellville’s Taylor Case and Versailles’ Hannah Hoxworth. 
Outfield: Blair Oaks’ Hannah Schroeder, Russellville’s McKendra Fischer and Eugene’s Ally Puckett. 
Pitchers: Blair Oaks’ Payton Staggs, Eugene’s Lexi Dickerson and Warsaw’s Taylor Hetherington. 
Catchers: Eugene’s Rachael Surface and Russellville’s Brooke Kremer. 
Utility: Blair Oaks’ Lydia Pointer. ﻿
